Now we choose our plaintext
Since this is a *chosen plaintext* attack, we have access to the encryption being used and we can run whatever plaintext we want through the algorithm to get its cipher text. What we want to do is choose two plaintext messages whose differential is equal to the input differential that we found last step. These two messages must also produce two ciphertexts whose differential is equal to the output differential we found last step.
